Graph Theory
Nodes, Edges, Destinations
There are two main ways computers "traverse" or search through a map:

Breadth-First Search (BFS): Exploring all the closest rooms first (like checking every room 1 step away, then every room 2 steps away).

Depth-First Search (DFS): Picking one path and following it as deep as it goes until you hit a dead end, then backtracking.
